(thirdQuint)Choline Quantification in Breast Cancer by MRS.

 1.

 Establishment of new MRS sequence for choline quantification of choline.

 This sequence is choline-selective, and signals from water and lipids are suppressed simultaneously.

 2.

 Compare to different methods for choline quantification.

 The first method is quantification through an external phantom standard, containing a known concentration of choline.

 The other method is based on the utilisation of internal water signal as a reference.

 Both calculations can be performed from the same MR exam.

 Ten patients will be included in the study.

